@Darkless012 is very close, but not quite right.  The whole parallelism thing is documented in some detail [here](http://streamparse.readthedocs.io/en/master/topologies.html#parallelism), but the basic idea is the parallelism hint for a particular component, which for a Python component is the number of Python processes that will run in the topology for that component.  The `-p N` flag sets the number of workers and ackers, which is basically the number of JVM processes that Storm will use for the entire topology.  

These are different things, and you should set `-p` to the number of machines in your cluster, like @Darkless012 said.

I apologize for quickly misreading the issue the first time, but I'm closing this since it's just a misunderstanding.

