@devashishsharma2302 The version of jinjasql which replaces with an underscore has not yet been pushed to pypi. On version 0.1.6 it's currently using `#` as a delimiter not `_`.
Because of this jinjasql will fail when trying to execute in sqlalchemy using named parameters, as `#` is not considered a valid character in sqlalchemy bind parameters.
I would guess that issue is happening here, since `engine` looks sqlalchemy like. 🤔

